AIRCRAFT DEPARTED IN VFR CONDITIONS FOR SHORT X-COUNTRY FLIGHT. NO WEATHER 
BRIEFING WAS OBTAINED. ON INITIAL ENCOUNTER WITH DETERIORATING CEILING 
AND VISIBILITY CONDITIONS, PILOT REDUCED ALTITUDE IN ATTEMPT TO MAINTAIN 
GROUND REFERENCE. COURSE REVERSAL NOT INITIATED UNTIL GROUND 
REFERENCE LOST. PILOT CITED DISORIENTATION IN TURN AND STALL AS CAUSE OF 
LOSS OF CONTROL. WX REPORTED AT PELLSTON, MI, (30 MI S), WAS 3 MI VISIBILITY, 
800 FEET THIN BKN, 4000 FEET OVC. 
